"title": "1070: God, joy of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1070",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God rejoices in the well-being and faithfulness of his covenant people, and in the repentance and conversion of sinners. He brings joy to his people, who rejoice in his presence and faithfulness.</p>\n<h2>God is the source of joy</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:4\">PSA 37:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:1\">1SA 2:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:11\">NEH 1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:43\">NEH 12:43</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:10\">ISA 61:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:11\">JHN 15:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:4\">PHP 4:4</a></p>\n<h2>God rejoices in the restoration of his people</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:41\">JER 32:41</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa62:4-Isa62:5\">ISA 62:4–62:5</a> <em>He rejoices as does a bridegroom</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:19\">ISA 65:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:20\">JER 31:20</a> <em>He rejoices as does a father</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:17\">ZEP 3:17</a></p>\n<h2>Joy can be found in the heavenly presence of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:27\">1CH 16:27</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:4-Job38:7\">JOB 38:4–38:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov8:30-Prov8:31\">PRO 8:30–8:31</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:7\">LUK 15:7</a> <em>over sinners who repent</em></p>\n<h2>Causes of God's joy</h2>\n<h3>His own works</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:24\">JER 9:24</a></p>\n<h3>His chosen servant</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:18\">MAT 12:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:1\">ISA 42:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:9\">HEB 1:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:7\">PSA 45:7</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:17\">MAT 3:17</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:11\">MRK 1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:22\">LUK 3:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:5\">MAT 17:5</a></p>\n<h3>The restored temple</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:8\">HAG 1:8</a></p>\n<h3>His people and their worship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps149:4-Ps149:9\">PSA 149:4–149:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:30-Ps69:31\">PSA 69:30–69:31</a></p>\n<h3>Repentance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut30:9\">DEU 30:9</a></p>\n<h3>Obedience, honesty and integrity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:22\">1SA 15:22</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov12:22\">PRO 12:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:17\">1CH 29:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps147:10-Ps147:11\">PSA 147:10–147:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:1\">PRO 11:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:20\">PRO 11:20</a></p>\n<h2>God's face shining on his people</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:25\">NUM 6:25</a></strong> <em>When God's face shines on his people his divine pleasure and joy is implied.</em> \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps67:1\">PSA 67:1</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps80:19\">PSA 80:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:135\">PSA 119:135</a>PSA <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:16\">34:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:12\">1PE 3:12</a></p>",
